:::summary
Astronomy is the oldest science — the study of celestial objects, space, and the physical universe as a whole — practiced by every civilization in human history and cherished by the Christian tradition as the discipline that reveals the glory of God written in the heavens. From the ancient Babylonians charting planetary movements to Copernicus's heliocentric revolution, Galileo's telescope, and the modern discovery of billions of galaxies, astronomy has repeatedly expanded the human sense of wonder and confirmed the Psalmist's declaration: "The heavens declare the glory of God."
:::

